<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" class="marketing">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <meta name="description" content="Very Good AdBlock is a fast Manifest V3 ad blocker for Chrome and Firefox that removes ads, pop-ups, and YouTube and Twitch interruptions at the source. No telemetry.">
    <meta name="theme-color" content="#100a0b">
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://verygoodadblock.org/">
    <script>
      // Set the theme before first paint (no flash): saved choice, else system.
      (function () {
        try {
          var saved = localStorage.getItem('vga-theme')
          var theme = saved || (matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: light)').matches ? 'light' : 'dark')
          document.documentElement.dataset.theme = theme
        }
        catch (e) {}
      })()
    </script>
    <meta property="og:type" content="website">
    <meta property="og:site_name" content="Very Good AdBlock">
    <meta property="og:url" content="https://verygoodadblock.org/">
    <meta property="og:title" content="Very Good AdBlock — fast, private ad blocker for Chrome & Firefox">
    <meta property="og:description" content="A fast Manifest V3 ad blocker for Chrome and Firefox that removes ads, pop-ups, and YouTube and Twitch interruptions at the source. No telemetry.">
    <meta property="og:image" content="https://verygoodadblock.org/icons/icon-128.png">
    <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary">
    <meta name="twitter:title" content="Very Good AdBlock — fast, private ad blocker for Chrome & Firefox">
    <meta name="twitter:description" content="Removes ads, pop-ups, and YouTube and Twitch interruptions at the source. No telemetry.">
    <meta name="twitter:image" content="https://verygoodadblock.org/icons/icon-128.png">
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="48x48" href="/icons/icon-48.png">
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/icons/icon.svg">
    <title>Very Good AdBlock — fast, private ad blocker for Chrome &amp; Firefox</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css">
  </head>
  <body class="marketing-shell">
    <header class="marketing-nav" aria-label="Primary navigation">
      <div class="marketing-nav-inner">
        <a class="brand-lockup" href="#top" aria-label="Very Good AdBlock home">
          <span class="brand-mark" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <span>Very Good AdBlock</span>
        </a>
        <nav>
          <div class="nav-item has-menu">
            <a class="nav-link" href="features/" aria-haspopup="true" aria-expanded="false">Features</a>
            <div class="nav-menu" role="menu" aria-label="Features">
              <a class="nav-menu-item" href="features/#network-blocking" role="menuitem">
                <span class="nav-menu-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                  <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 3 4 6v5c0 4.4 3.1 8.3 8 9.5 4.9-1.2 8-5.1 8-9.5V6l-8-3Z"></path><path d="m9 12 2 2 4-4"></path></svg>
                </span>
                <span class="nav-menu-text"><strong>Network blocking</strong><small>14,000+ ad and tracker hosts stopped at the request</small></span>
              </a>
              <a class="nav-menu-item" href="features/#youtube-twitch" role="menuitem">
                <span class="nav-menu-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                  <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="3" y="5" width="18" height="14" rx="3"></rect><path d="m10 9 5 3-5 3V9Z"></path></svg>
                </span>
                <span class="nav-menu-text"><strong>YouTube and Twitch</strong><small>Video ads removed at the source, player untouched</small></span>
              </a>
              <a class="nav-menu-item" href="features/#popups" role="menuitem">
                <span class="nav-menu-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                  <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="3" y="5" width="18" height="14" rx="2"></rect><path d="M3 9h18"></path><path d="m9.5 12.5 5 5M14.5 12.5l-5 5"></path></svg>
                </span>
                <span class="nav-menu-text"><strong>Pop-ups and pop-unders</strong><small>Click-hijack windows neutralized, real ones allowed</small></span>
              </a>
              <a class="nav-menu-item" href="features/#controls" role="menuitem">
                <span class="nav-menu-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                  <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M4 8h10M18 8h2M4 16h2M10 16h10"></path><circle cx="16" cy="8" r="2.4"></circle><circle cx="8" cy="16" r="2.4"></circle></svg>
                </span>
                <span class="nav-menu-text"><strong>Control and privacy</strong><small>Pause per site, allowlists, local-only stats</small></span>
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <a class="nav-link" href="#how">How it works</a>
          <a class="nav-link" href="#privacy">Privacy</a>
        </nav>
        <div class="nav-controls">
          <a class="nav-icon" href="https://github.com/chrisbbreuer/very-good-adblock" target="_blank" rel="noopener" aria-label="GitHub repository" title="GitHub">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
              <path d="M12 .5A11.5 11.5 0 0 0 8.36 22.9c.57.1.78-.25.78-.55v-2c-3.2.7-3.88-1.36-3.88-1.36-.52-1.33-1.28-1.68-1.28-1.68-1.05-.72.08-.7.08-.7 1.16.08 1.77 1.2 1.77 1.2 1.03 1.77 2.7 1.26 3.36.96.1-.75.4-1.26.73-1.55-2.56-.29-5.25-1.28-5.25-5.7 0-1.26.45-2.29 1.2-3.1-.13-.29-.52-1.46.1-3.05 0 0 .97-.31 3.18 1.18a11 11 0 0 1 5.8 0c2.2-1.5 3.17-1.18 3.17-1.18.63 1.59.24 2.76.12 3.05.75.81 1.2 1.84 1.2 3.1 0 4.43-2.7 5.4-5.27 5.69.42.36.78 1.06.78 2.14v3.17c0 .3.2.66.79.55A11.5 11.5 0 0 0 12 .5Z"/>
            </svg>
          </a>
          <button id="theme-toggle" class="theme-toggle" type="button" aria-label="Toggle color theme" title="Toggle light/dark">
            <svg class="theme-icon theme-icon-sun" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" aria-hidden="true">
              <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="4"></circle>
              <path d="M12 2v2M12 20v2M4.93 4.93l1.41 1.41M17.66 17.66l1.41 1.41M2 12h2M20 12h2M6.34 17.66l-1.41 1.41M19.07 4.93l-1.41 1.41"></path>
            </svg>
            <svg class="theme-icon theme-icon-moon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
              <path d="M21 12.79A9 9 0 1 1 11.21 3 7 7 0 0 0 21 12.79z"></path>
            </svg>
          </button>
          <a class="nav-action" href="docs/">Read docs</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <main id="top">
      <section class="marketing-hero">
        <div class="hero-copy">
          <p class="eyebrow">Chrome &amp; Firefox · Manifest V3</p>
          <h1>Ads gone before the page loads.</h1>
          <p class="hero-lede">
            Very Good AdBlock removes ads, pop-ups, and YouTube and Twitch interruptions at the source,
            then stays out of the way. No telemetry, no bloat.
          </p>
          <div class="hero-actions">
            <a class="primary-link" href="docs/guide/install/">Install locally</a>
            <a class="secondary-link" href="#how">How it works</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="hero-visual">
          <!-- The real popup component, inlined at build time from
               pages/partials/popup-preview.html (generated off the shipping popup). -->
          <div class="hero-device" id="popup-preview" role="img" aria-label="The Very Good AdBlock toolbar popup: 47 ads blocked on this page, 8.4 GB of data saved, 20 hours of video time recovered, and a chart of the last 24 hours."></div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="features" class="marketing-band">
        <div class="section-kicker">
          <h2>Protection at the source, not fragile page rewrites.</h2>
          <a class="section-link" href="features/">All features →</a>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-grid">
          <a class="feature-card" href="features/#network-blocking">
            <span class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 3 4 6v5c0 4.4 3.1 8.3 8 9.5 4.9-1.2 8-5.1 8-9.5V6l-8-3Z"></path><path d="m9 12 2 2 4-4"></path></svg>
            </span>
            <h3>Network blocking</h3>
            <p>Manifest V3 declarative rules stop 14,000+ ad, tracker, and annoyance hosts before the request completes.</p>
            <span class="feature-more">Learn more →</span>
          </a>
          <a class="feature-card" href="features/#youtube-twitch">
            <span class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="3" y="5" width="18" height="14" rx="3"></rect><path d="m10 9 5 3-5 3V9Z"></path></svg>
            </span>
            <h3>YouTube and Twitch</h3>
            <p>Strips video ads out of YouTube's player response, skips what slips through, and detects Twitch stream ads. The real video never breaks.</p>
            <span class="feature-more">Learn more →</span>
          </a>
          <a class="feature-card" href="features/#popups">
            <span class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="3" y="5" width="18" height="14" rx="2"></rect><path d="M3 9h18"></path><path d="m9.5 12.5 5 5M14.5 12.5l-5 5"></path></svg>
            </span>
            <h3>Pop-ups and pop-unders</h3>
            <p>Neutralizes the click-hijack pop-ups streaming and file-host sites open, including the ones fired from inside the player iframe.</p>
            <span class="feature-more">Learn more →</span>
          </a>
          <a class="feature-card" href="features/#controls">
            <span class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M4 8h10M18 8h2M4 16h2M10 16h10"></path><circle cx="16" cy="8" r="2.4"></circle><circle cx="8" cy="16" r="2.4"></circle></svg>
            </span>
            <h3>Control and privacy</h3>
            <p>Pause per site, keep an allowlist, hide cookie banners, and read local stats from a clean dashboard. Nothing leaves your machine.</p>
            <span class="feature-more">Learn more →</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="get" class="browsers-band">
        <div class="browsers-copy">
          <p class="eyebrow">Get it</p>
          <h2>Runs on Chrome and Firefox.</h2>
          <p>One codebase, a browser-specific Manifest V3 build. Load it today, or grab it from the stores the moment it lands.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="browser-buttons">
          <!-- Swap these hrefs for the Chrome Web Store / Firefox AMO listing URLs
               once the extension is published; they point at the install guide today. -->
          <a class="browser-button" href="docs/guide/install/" aria-label="Get Very Good AdBlock for Chrome">
            <img class="browser-logo" src="https://cdn.simpleicons.org/googlechrome" alt="" width="34" height="34" loading="lazy">
            <span class="browser-text"><strong>Get it for Chrome</strong><small>Chrome, Edge, Brave, Arc</small></span>
          </a>
          <a class="browser-button" href="docs/guide/install/" aria-label="Get Very Good AdBlock for Firefox">
            <img class="browser-logo" src="https://cdn.simpleicons.org/firefoxbrowser" alt="" width="34" height="34" loading="lazy">
            <span class="browser-text"><strong>Get it for Firefox</strong><small>Firefox 140 and up</small></span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="how" class="how-band">
        <h2>Running in about a minute.</h2>
        <ol class="how-steps">
          <li>
            <span class="how-num">1</span>
            <h3>Install</h3>
            <p>Load it into Chrome or Firefox. One codebase, a browser-specific build, no account.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="how-num">2</span>
            <h3>Pin it</h3>
            <p>The toolbar icon shows exactly what got blocked on the page in front of you.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="how-num">3</span>
            <h3>Browse</h3>
            <p>Ads, pop-ups, and video interruptions are gone before the page can render them.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <section id="stats" class="stats-showcase">
        <div>
          <h2>Local stats make the blocking visible.</h2>
          <p>
            Lifetime blocks, a daily history, estimated bandwidth saved, and estimated video minutes recovered.
            Compact totals sync across your installs; the detailed history stays on the device.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-wall" aria-label="Very Good AdBlock stats examples">
          <article>
            <strong>52,910</strong>
            <span>lifetime blocks</span>
          </article>
          <article>
            <strong>8.4 GB</strong>
            <span>estimated data saved</span>
          </article>
          <article>
            <strong>19.6 hr</strong>
            <span>estimated video time saved</span>
          </article>
          <article>
            <strong>0</strong>
            <span>remote telemetry events</span>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="privacy" class="privacy-band">
        <div class="privacy-copy">
          <h2>No hidden telemetry. No remote rule surprises.</h2>
          <p>
            Rules ship with each release and refresh daily from a public list built from pinned filter revisions. Your site choices become local rules,
            and the dashboard marks every estimate as an estimate. Nothing about your browsing is sent anywhere.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="privacy-list">
          <div><span></span>Chrome MV3 declarativeNetRequest</div>
          <div><span></span>Site-specific cosmetic hiding, kill switch included</div>
          <div><span></span>Local and sync storage split</div>
          <div><span></span>Exportable stats and reset controls</div>
        </div>
      </section>
      <section class="cta-band">
        <div class="cta-inner">
          <span class="cta-badge">Free and open source</span>
          <h2>Browse like the ads were never there.</h2>
          <p>MIT licensed, Chrome and Firefox from one codebase, with no account and no telemetry. Read the code, file an issue, or send a pull request.</p>
          <div class="hero-actions">
            <a class="primary-link" href="docs/guide/install/">Install locally</a>
            <a class="secondary-link" href="https://github.com/chrisbbreuer/very-good-adblock" target="_blank" rel="noopener">View source</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="subscribe" class="subscribe-band">
        <div class="subscribe-inner">
          <h2>Know the moment it hits the stores.</h2>
          <p>One email when Very Good AdBlock lands on the Chrome Web Store and Firefox Add-ons. No spam, unsubscribe anytime.</p>
          <form class="subscribe-form" id="subscribe-form" action="https://stacksjs.com/api/email/subscribe" method="POST">
            <input type="email" id="subscribe-email" name="email" placeholder="you@example.com" autocomplete="email" aria-label="Email address" required>
            <input type="hidden" name="source" value="verygoodadblock">
            <button class="primary-link" type="submit">Notify me</button>
          </form>
          <p class="subscribe-status" id="subscribe-status" role="status" aria-live="polite"></p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer class="marketing-footer">
      <span>Very Good AdBlock</span>
      <a href="docs/">Docs</a>
      <a href="docs/guide/usage/">Usage</a>
      <a href="https://github.com/chrisbbreuer/very-good-adblock" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>
      <a href="https://bsky.app/profile/stacksjs.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Bluesky</a>
    </footer>
    <script type="module" src="/marketing.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
